Claude Monet (First Impression)
Harry N. Abrams, Inc. | 1991 | ISBN: 0810936208 | English | 96 pages | PDF | 15 MB

Claude Monet drew with ease as a teenager, but hated the idea o f landscape painting. Influenced by two older artists, he explored the world of nature, of sunlight and color, of water, trees, and flowers and became world renowned as a pioneer of Impressionism
